post_text:
Beginning Monday, September 14th, breakfast and lunch for all students at Tecumseh Local Schools in grades K-12 will be free. We have received a waiver from the Ohio Department of Education for this opportunity.

This includes the food on the lunch buses currently going out to satellite locations throughout the district. All students can pick up five free breakfasts and lunches from the buses per week. The student or the parent will need to provide the name of the student, building he or she attends and the four-digit pin number to receive the free food. Students do not need to be present if the parent/older sibling knows the PIN number. If you are planning to secure food from the satellite bus program, you need to notify the Child Nutrition Office at 845-4519. This will help ensure we have enough food on each bus.

When students do return to school, the free breakfast and lunch will continue until the end of December 2020.

If you have any questions, please reach out to the Child Nutrition Department at 845-4519.

post_text:
It is with a heavy heart that we share the passing of one of our Arrows this week. Mr. Guil Herrick, math teacher and department chair, passed away unexpectedly this week. Mr. Herrick was an excellent educator, with a wonderful sense of humor and a member of the District Technology Committee. He often helped his fellow colleagues at the high school and throughout the district with technology tips. He will be missed by his colleagues and students that he positively impacted with his presence. Please help us keep his family in your thoughts during this time. We will miss you Guil.
"Once an Arrow ~ Always an Arrow....."

post_text: The Chromebook pick-up for Tecumseh Middle and Tecumseh High School students who have been assigned a device, will take place tomorrow August 25th from 9:00 - 1:00 AND 5:00 - 7:00 p.m. at the front tower doors of the high school. We would prefer that the devices be picked up between 9:00 - 1:00 as we will have more individuals available at this time to help. post_text: Many have asked about the yearbooks that were ordered last year for the elementary and middle schools. This is a letter from Lifetouch that we'd like to share. We will post any information as it becomes available regarding yearbook orders. If you can please share this information, it would be greatly appreciated. Thank you!

post_text: Parents of all incoming Kindergarten students should have received an email last Wednesday afternoon with their child's teacher assignment, kindergarten assessment day and time, supply list, etc. The email was sent to the email address used when registering the student in our online registration system. Please check your spam/junk folder for this email address if you did not receive it. If you still are unable to locate your emailed letter, please email Mrs. Strader at karyl.strader@tecumsehlocal.org and she will resend the letter to you. If you can please share, it would be greatly appreciated! Thank you!

post_text: Next Wednesday, July 22nd, a new pair of shoes will be available for any child in our community needing a pair, while supplies last. If you are interested, please come to Tecumseh High School between 10:00 - 10:30. Please follow the designated route to the front of the high school and remain in your car. Volunteers will come to your car and ask for your child's shoe size and deliver these to you on site. Thank you to the combined efforts of the Clark County Sheriff's Department and Shoes for the Shoeless for this wonderful opportunity for the children of our community. If you can please share this information, it would be greatly appreciated. Thank you!

Congratulations to Tecumseh Middle School student, Ronan Weaver! Ronan received a visit from several TMS Seventh Grade Teachers recently and was presented with the "Stand Up and Own It" Award. The Stand Up and Own It Award is given to students who take responsibility for their actions and attitudes by striving for an “Above the Line” response in all situations. These students are people who do the right thing even when others are not watching. Students were nominated by their fellow peers for the award. Way to go, Ronan! We are proud of your efforts.

Please help us congratulate Jillian Sarihan! Jillian is one of the Class of 2020 Valedictorians! Jillian Sarihan is the daughter of Alper and Jennifer Sarihan. In her time at Tecumseh, she was the Vice President of National Honor Society, a six year cross country runner, a four year cheerleader, and a two year AFJROTC cadet. In her free time, you can find her fishing, powerlifting, or wakeboarding. She plans to attend Bowling Green State University in the fall to major in biology and, ultimately, become an optometrist. We are very proud of you Jillian! Best of luck on your journey.

Please see information on summer food opportunities for students in our community provided by Impact Bethel. Thank you Impact Bethel for continuing to provide summer food programs for our children! Additionally, Second Harvest Food Pantry will distribute food from New Carlisle Elementary School beginning Wednesday, June 17th at 1:00 p.m. and each Wednesday following throughout the summer. They will offer breakfast and lunch items for the week. We are fortunate to have these opportunities available for our children!

post_text: Please help us wish a Happy Retirement to Mrs. Ann Snyder. Mrs. Snyder had retired previously from another district, but came to Tecumseh for the past three years as a Gifted Intervention Specialist at Donnelsville and New Carlisle Elementary School. This school year she additionally worked with twenty-eight teachers on Professional Development on teaching gifted students. When asked if she had special memories to share, Mrs. Snyder replied, "My favorite memory begins with a really rough start to my first school year - but the memory contains amazing support from co-workers. Of course I will always carry with me those aha moments in the classroom, all the times students were excited about… More

Although we didn't anticipate March 13th being our last day for our students, we tried to make the best of it! Amongst smiles, waves, and a few tears, the elementary staff members said goodbye to their students today with a send off parade. We will share photos of the parades at each elementary school over the next several days. We will miss our students very much, but we are looking forward to seeing them again very soon! Stay safe and enjoy the summer!

All elementary students are invited to parade in cars TODAY at each building to mark our last day of school. Feel free to make signs but realize that we can't exchange anything during this parade. We miss you so much and can't wait to see you all! All of your teachers will be at school ready to wave to you. If you have not picked up school supplies and dropped off library and baggy books,please bring those books! Self serve pickup and drop off at each building.
Park Layne Elementary 4:30 - 5:30 pm
New Carlisle Elementary 5:00 - 6:00 pm
Donnelsville Elementary 5:30 - 6:30 pm

Assistant High School Principals, Mr. Foster and Mr. Hauf and our Athletic Director, Mr. Eier, have faithfully helped with the Lunch Bus since the inception of the program. Most weeks, they ride the bus and help distribute the food. Today was quite a soggy distribution day. These gentlemen were given a bracelet with the words, "The Tecumseh Way!" on it for going above and beyond to help the children in need in our community. Thank you for your routine heart for service and thank you for being in the soaking rain for quite awhile today. We appreciate you!

When asked if she could share special memories from her time at Tecumseh, Mrs. Meadors expressed, "Special memories.......those will be held in my heart forever....the small successes that I saw with my students that will never show up on a state test, but regardless, brought a smile to their faces and mine, along with a sense of pride each time they accomplished something that we had been working on, for what seemed like an… More

Please help us wish a Happy Retirement to Ms. Rhonda Ball! Ms. Ball has worked at Tecumseh Local Schools for a total of nine years. She was hired in 1985 fresh out of college. She taught as a math teacher until 1989. She blessed us with her return to the district in 2015, serving once again as a math teacher at Tecumseh High School. Additionally she served as the TEA building representative and the Sophomore Class Advisor for several years.
When asked if she has any fond memories, Ms. Ball reflected, " I have many fond memories of my time at THS, some of which include meeting Ms. Michelle Peters in the copy room on my first day back at THS in 2015. Little did I know that we would become… More

post_text:
Please help us congratulate our Air Force JROTC Unit OH-881st at Tecumseh High School for earning the Distinguished Unit with Merit Award for academic year 2019-2020! The award recognizes the personal growth and accomplishments of our cadets, the contributions of the instructors as mentors of the cadets and the support of the school and community. The Distinguished Unit with Merit Award is limited to the very best of the nation's 890 Air Force JROTC Units. This is the 17th year in a row the program has received the Distinguished Unit Award and the fourth year they have received this award with Merit. Way to go to all of our cadets, Major Couch and Chief Franklin! We are proud of you for representing your program, the district, our community and the nation in such an exemplary manner.
Arrow STRONG!

This week is designated as our Annual Staff Appreciation Week! Although we greatly appreciate all of our staff members everyday of the year, we set aside a special week to celebrate them. Each day is designated to a group(s) of staff members. (Administrative Assistant Day was April 24th). Today is designated to our Child Nutrition Employees! Thank you all for providing nutritious meals for our students throughout the year! We appreciate each one of you! An additional thank you to the personnel from this department who have helped make sandwiches for the Lunch Bus during the district closure.
We are Arrow STRONG!

We are asking for your help please to show appreciation for all of our staff members at Tecumseh Local Schools. We are inviting our students to write a note or draw a picture thanking our staff members. You can send your note or drawing, along with a photo of the student if you'd like, to Paula Crew at paula.crew@tecumsehlocal.org. We will post these on our Facebook Page. Thank you all!
Arrow PRIDE!

One of our school buses, adorned with banners and messages of well-wishes for our 2020 Seniors, is parked in front of Tecumseh High School today, Saturday, May 2nd, until 5:00 p.m. Some students were at work or unavailable to come outside when we came around yesterday delivering signs. You are welcome to come to the parking lot and take photos with your child in front of the bus if you wish. Please make sure if multiple families arrive simultaneously to maintain social distance. If you could please share, so the maximum number of individuals are aware of this opportunity, it would be greatly appreciated.
Thank you!

post_text: We would like to extend our immense appreciation and Happy Retirement to Mr. John Heinl. Mr. Heinl began his career at Tecumseh Local Schools as a science teacher during the 1975-76 school year. During his teaching years, he taught Life Science, Physical Science, and Earth Science. In 1993-94, he began serving students in a new capacity as a middle school guidance counselor at Olive Branch, taking over for his good friend, Bill Buckles. For the past decade, he has served as a guidance counselor at Tecumseh High School. Mr. Heinl served as a varsity assistant football coach under the head coaches of Bob Hartley, Bruce Schibler, Larry Baldridge, and Mike Lucas and was the assistant varsity… More

Dear Tecumseh Local Families,

I would like to update you on information regarding the schedule for the remainder of the year, please.

Originally, May 8th, 15th and 22nd were embedded in the school calendar as days off for this year to be used as make up calamity days, if needed. We will now use these dates as instructional/enrichment dates and the last official student day will be May 27th.

The last day classwork will be assigned to our students will be Monday, May 11th. Students will have until May 22nd to complete any assignments given for the week of May 11th and any outstanding assignments from previous weeks they may need to make up. On May 18th, enrichment activities will be made…
